  Ondo State Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, has said that the newly appointed Chief of Staff to President Muhammadu Buhari, Ambassador Ibrahim Gambari, would not disappoint Nigerians. Governor Akeredolu who hailed the appointment as a round peg in a round hole, in view of Gambari’s experience in both national and global politics said the Ambassador’s long public career and a university teacher would come in handy in his new role. In a press statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Segun Ajiboye, Akeredolu stated that Ambassador Gambari would bring his wealth of experience to enhance the good works of the President and his cabinet. The Governor thanked the President for his choice, adding that the appointment of Gambari showed President Buhari as a leader who meant well for the nation. 